<hr size=1> An Ethiopian, a Canadian, and an American are all walking down the beach in sunny southern California one saturday morning, when the Ethiopian spies something half buried in the sand.<br>
<br>
The Canadian bends over and picks it up... and the American takes it from him and rubs the sand off of it to reveal a golden oil lamp.  As he's rubbing it, smoke begins to billow out from the end of the lamp, and *POOF*, a genie appears!<br>
<br>
&quot;I am the genie of the lamp... and I am here to grant you three wishes... but seeing since there are three of you, that is only one wish each!&quot;<br>
<br>
The three talk it over, and agree that since the Ethiopian saw it first, he could wish first...<br>
<br>
&quot;Well Mr. Genie sir... you see... where I come from, hunger runs rampant, and there isn't enough food to feed everyone... my wish is for you to make the lands in my country fertile and ripe to support agriculture to support and feed my people...&quot;<br>
<br>
With a rumble of thunder in the sky... the Genie says, &quot;It is done&quot;<br>
<br>
The Canadian, upon hearing this, states that he should go next, since he was the one who picked up the lamp...<br>
<br>
&quot;Genie... where I'm from, its a wonderful beautiful country, and we are at peace and desire nothing more but to be left alone... especially from those loud mouthed, filthy americans... I wish you would make everyone who isn't Canadian leave and then build a wall all around Canada that won't let anything in or out so we can be the best place in the world all by ourselves...&quot;<br>
<br>
With a flash of lightning, the Genie says &quot;It is done.&quot;<br>
<br>
The American, looking down at the sand, says, &quot;Tell me a little about this wall you just put around Canada, Genie...&quot;<br>
<br>
The Genie says, &quot;Its 15 miles high, and 30 miles thick... and nothing can get in or out.&quot;<br>
<br>
Upon hearing this.. .the American turns to the Canadian and says to the Genie, &quot;Cool... fill it with water...&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
